            <h3>Men’s Dialogues As A Tool In The Fight Against GBV And HIV In Lesotho</h3>
            <p>In the beginning of 2023 two organizations partnered with male leaders in Lesotho to initiate men’s dialogues to discuss and find solutions to the factors that drive violence against women and girls and HIV infections in the Southern African nation. 
 
                UN Women South Africa Multi-Country Office, enabled by funds from UNAIDS Unified Budget, Results and Accountability Framework (UBRAF), supported women’s rights organization Gem Institute Lesotho and the Christian Council of Lesotho (CCL).  
                
                </p>
        </div>
